getFieldDescriptor

public FieldDescriptor getFieldDescriptor(Store store,
                                          java.beans.PropertyDescriptor pd)
Gets a field descriptor for a property if its compile-time type is a primitive type, a boxed primitive type, String, java.util.Date, java.sql.Date, java.sql.Timestamp, java.sql.Time, java.sql.Blob, byte[], or Persistent. For any other types, this method returns null.
